extends _templates/main
block vars
		- var title = 'What Tools do I use?'
		- var description = 'Jason Lydon: a wordy version of my intro'
		- var keywords = 'jade,node,gulp,json,static site generation'
		- var pageClass = 'tools'

block content 
	h1 Tools of my trade
	p Read through the table below to get a sense of the tools I used or have used and my level of skill with each of them. But first, check out my web nerd version of "A Rifleman's Creed"
	aside.poem
		h1 Pixelman's Creed
		p
			| - This is my website. There are many like it, but this one is mine. -
			br
			| - My website is my best friend. It is my life. I must master it as I must master my life. -
			br
			| - My website, without me, is useless. Without my website, I am useless. I must layout my modules true. I must compress finer than my rival who is trying to minify me. I must render him before he lossy's me. I will... -
			br
			| - My website and I know that what counts in browsers is not the lines we write, the ease of our tween, nor the gradients we make. We know that it is the hits that count. We will hit... -
			br
			| - My markup is human, even as I, because it is my life. Thus, I will learn it as a brother. I will learn its weaknesses, its strength, its parts, its accessories, its APIs and its libraries. I will keep my code clean and ready, even as I am clean and ready. We will become part of each other. We will... -
			br
			| - Before W3C, I swear this creed. My internet and I are the defenders of our ideas. We are the masters of our clients. We are the requests of my life. -
			br
			| - So be it, until victory is America's and there is no buffering, but peace! -
	table
		thead
			tr
				th TOOL
				th HOW
				th WHEN
				th QUE?
		tbody
			tr
				th(colspan="4") MARKUP
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/html.png" alt="HTML")
				td Hand written, snippets, patterns
				td Daily
				td I am a man of semantics. Clean, basic code makes me happy.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/php.png" alt="PHP")
				td Hand written, snippets, patterns, variables, functions, database connections
				td Daily
				td There isn't anything Personal about these Home Pages...
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/jade.svg" alt="JADE")
				td Used as a templating engine via Gulp
				td Whenever I need to hand off HTML templates
				td Big fan of Jade. I was super psyched when I created a build for a company site using json.
			tr
				th(colspan="4") STYLES
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/css.png" alt="CSS")
				td Usually compiled via gulp
				td Daily
				td 
					| I've been cascading since before it was cool. "Do you use divs?" "You don't use tables?" And now there is no support for IE9. And FLEXBOX, flexbox.
					br
					| Do you remember when #d0d0d0; was the first shade of grey a monitor could pick up?
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/stylus.svg" alt="Stylus")
				td My favorite preprocessor.
				td Daily
				td Loops! Loose punctuation! No `ruby` in the title of terminal. Just a few reasons Stylus has quickly become my favorite. We'll see where it stands once I get into PostCSS...
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/sass.svg" alt="Sass")
				td Sass used to be the cool kid.
				td Daily
				td Sass is still on projects I work on, but not projects I start.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/less.png" alt="LESS")
				td LESS is javascript, which makes it cooler that Sass.
				td Daily
				td Somewhere in the middle.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/postcss.png" alt="PostCSS")
					br
					| PostCSS
				td This website is my first PostCSS build.
				td In progress
				td I'm digging PostCSS. It does everything that makes Stylus my favorite, except it's easier to write custom functions.
			tr
				th(colspan="4") FUNCTIONALITY
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/javascript.png" alt="Javacript")
				td Hand written, core language
				td Daily
				td I like knowing how the language works, so I use the core language, poach functions when I need them and polyfill when required.
			tr
				td Velocity.js
				td Contains the parts of jQuery I miss.
				td Daily
				td What do I miss from jQuery? animate(); slideUp(); slideDown(); Velocity's got it.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/jquery.png" alt="jQuery")
				td with lots of dollar signs
				td when I inherit a project using it, otherwise, I skip it.
				td jQuery was my gateway drug to core Javascript. Once I looked under the hood (and was called a sucker on G+), there was no going back for me.			
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/backbone.png" alt="Backbone")
				td The least amount of bias
				td Still demo-ing
				td I'm a fan and I'm making up projects just to use backbone.js, I want more experience with it before I use it on a client site.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/react.png" alt="react")
				td Web Components, hell yes.
				td Tutorial-ing
				td Another library I want to use in production once I get a little deeper.
			tr
				th(colspan="4") WEB ANIMATIONS
			tr
				td: img(src="/public/img/tools/css.png" alt="CSS")
				td CSS3 Animations
				td Daily
				td Since I abide by lean methodologies, I must start by making all animations as CSS as possible. stroke-dasharray and stroke-dashoffset are my true allies.
			tr
				td Web Animation API
				td The future client API and the current polyfill. The WAAPI merges the animation engines of CSS and javascript into one, which makes JS animations much more efficient.
				td Occasionally
				td I built a pretty massive page to demo WAAPI. The future looks grand.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/snapsvg.svg" alt="SnapSVG") 
					br
					| SnapSVG
				td When CSS won't cut it or I need a shape tween (Flash reference), this is my go to.
				td Occasionally
				td My first true SVG animation relationship, which I have been removing one by one from projects...
			tr
				th(colspan="4") DATA
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/mysql.svg" alt="MySQL")
				td MySQL, YourSQL
				td Regularly.
				td I prefer a gui, but I'll get in there any means necessary! ssh cli, PHP MyAdmin, Sequel Pro, MySQL Work Bench
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/json.png" alt="json")
					br
					| json
				td Not just cause we share a name
				td Daily
				td I use it for my prototypes, which often ends up being the final data.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/mongodb.png" alt="MongoDB")
				td Shards
				td Tutorials
				td I took their class and got the Web Dev certificate, but I haven't used MongoDB outsite of MEAN tutorials...
			tr
				td XML
				td json's ugly step child
				td whenever I inherit it
				td of course XML doesn't have a logo
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/svg.svg" alt="SVG")
				td Technically SVG is XML, which makes it data...
				td Daily
				td vector graphics are the present and future. I'm currently a huge fan of subtle SVG animations.
			tr
				th(colspan="4") SERVERS
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/apache.png" alt="Apache")
