				td Regularly
				td Pretty standard uses, usually rocking a htaccess or htpassword
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/nginx.png" alt="NGINX")
				td A few jobs ago, I would cli on the regular..
				td not too often
				td ...but now I work with a Dev Ops guy, so it's not my responsibility.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/nodejs.png" alt="nodejs")
				td Only locally
				td Daily
				td I used it for all my local builds, I use it to convert data. I just haven't used it on a hosted server.
			tr
				th(colspan="4") TASK MANAGERS
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/gulp.svg" alt="Gulp")
				td I'll take code over config!
				td Daily
				td Once I started with gulp, I never looked at Grunt the same!
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/grunt.svg" alt="Grunt")
				td My introduction to task managers.
				td not any more
				td I loved grunt, until I tried gulp.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/npm.svg" alt="npm")
				td npm init
				td dabbling
				td I've begun testing using the package.json as a task manager.
			tr
				th(colspan="4") CONTENT MANAGEMENT SYSTEMS
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/wordpress.png" alt="WordPress")
				td Only half the internet is on WordPress
				td Regularly
				td It's a love/hate relationship, but only because I respect it so much. Honestly, when it's the correct tool for the job, it's wonderful!
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/shopify.png" alt="Shopify")
				td Ecommerce's WordPress cousin?
				td Occasionally
				td Really impressed with Shopify's syncing app.
			tr
				td
					img(src="/public/img/tools/pimcore.png" alt="Pimcore")
				td PHP objects via the dashboard?!
				td been some time
				td I gave Pimcore it's own row because I really liked it when I was using it. I'd like to use it again.
			tr
				td Etc...
				td Symfony 2, Drupal, Code Igniter, Laravel, MODx, Expression Engine
				td Not in some time
				td It feels like I've worked on most CMS systems, usually building the templates.
